article.description:
Katie Douglas had 16 points and Nykesha Sales and
Adrienne Johnson each added 15 as the Connecticut Sun beat the
Phoenix Mercury 75-67 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Douglas, Sun hand Mercury fifth straight loss
article.linkText: Sun snap three-game skid with win vs. Mercury
article.story:
PHOENIX (AP) -- Katie Douglas had 16 points and Nykesha Sales and
Adrienne Johnson each added 15 as the Connecticut Sun beat the
Phoenix Mercury 75-67 on Saturday night.

Connecticut (10-11) snapped a three-game losing streak, sending
the Mercury (3-16) to their fifth straight loss.

"This win was huge," Sun coach Mike Thibault said. "When you
have only 14 games left in the season, the team that steals the
most road wins is going to have the advantage in the playoffs."

Johnson was 3-of-3 from 3-point range, and the Sun finished
7-of-11 overall from long range.

"We haven't shot the ball well for about three weeks,"
Thibault said. "Making the open shots and the easy shots is big. I
think we did a better job of that tonight."

Taj McWilliams-Franklin added 11 points and 10 rebounds for the
Sun. Anna DeForge had 18 points for the Mercury.

"We got outrebounded and that hurt us a lot," DeForge said.
"We needed to be a little more physical on the boards."
